          Dog

          Animal

          Description

          The dog or domestic dog is a domesticated descendant of the wolf which is characterized by an upturning tail. The dog is derived from an ancient, extinct wolf, and the modern wolf is the dog's nearest living relative. Wikipedia
          Gestation period: 58 – 68 days
          Lifespan: 10 – 13 years
          Height: 15 – 110 cm (At Shoulder)
          Daily sleep: 12 – 14 hours (Adult)
          Scientific name: Canis lupus familiaris
          Speed: German Shepherd: 48 km/h, Greyhound: 72 km/h
